list.item:
Notes and case histories which he assembled in the form of a compendium (
Taʿālīq wa-mujarrabāt jaʿalahā ʿalā jihat al-kunnāsh
). I – Ibn Abī Uṣaybiʿah – have found this work in his own handwriting, and in it he has an extensive discussion of diseases and their treatments. He writes at the beginning of the compendium what the purpose of it is: ‘I say that I, Ifrāʾīm, have composed this book to be a memorandum book in the form of a collection of items rather than a formal composition, as a warning against negligence for anyone who is treating diseases’.

On establishing by deduction that the production of phlegm increases in summer, while [the production of] blood and yellow bile [increases] in winter (
