M. fī ḥifẓ al-ṣiḥḥah
).

On diseases, their causes and their symptoms and treatments with simple and compound drugs (
K. fī l-amrāḍ wa-asbābihā wa-ʿalāmātihā wa-mudāwātihā bi-l-adwiyah al-mufradah wa-l-murakkabah
), the merits of which have proven successful from experience, and when the treatment is applied to a curable disease it is successful. The author gathered the information for this book from books on the art of medicine composed from the time of Adam to our time, organizing the scattered and miscellaneous materials.

